---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// JustGiving widget URL carried over from the previous site (CharityId
// 2927521). Lands the donor on the trust's JustGiving donation page.
// JustGiving handles Gift Aid for UK donors automatically.
//
// Future: CAF Donate is being considered as an alternative — see
// docs/donations.md and docs/todos.md.
const justGivingUrl =
  'https://widgets.justgiving.com/Button/Redirect?p=eyJJZCI6ImI5MzlkYWE1LTc5NTEtNDZlMi1hNTFkLWQwMzc5NDczODBhNyIsIkNoYXJpdHlJZCI6MjkyNzUyMSwiU2l6ZSI6ImwiLCJSZWZlcmVuY2UiOiJNSFR3ZWJzaXQiLCJUeXBlIjoiRG9uYXRlIn0=';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Donate"
  description="Support Mountain Heritage Trust. Donations fund our archivist, conservation work and the preservation of British mountaineering heritage."
>
  <article class="article">
    <h1>Donate</h1>
    <p class="article-summary">
      Help us preserve the stories, objects and archives of British mountaineering for
      future generations. Every donation directly funds our archivist, our collections
      care and our public exhibitions.
    </p>

    <div class="donate-cta">
      <a class="donate-button donate-button--large" href={justGivingUrl} rel="noopener">
        Donate via JustGiving
      </a>
      <p class="donate-cta-note">
        UK taxpayers — Gift Aid is collected automatically through JustGiving, increasing
        the value of your gift by 25% at no cost to you.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Why donate?</h2>
    <p>
      Britain has a rich mountaineering history. Mountain Heritage Trust holds a crucial
      part of this heritage — collections spanning the growth of rock climbing in the
      20th century, the great Himalayan expeditions, and the rise of indoor climbing
      walls. We actively curate and showcase this heritage, and target specific
      collections to grow the archive.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use your donation</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Funding a full-time archivist to manage and catalogue the collections.</li>
      <li>Training staff and volunteers in archival and conservation skills.</li>
      <li>Conserving and re-housing fragile material so it survives long-term.</li>
      <li>Supporting public exhibitions and learning resources.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Other ways to give</h2>

    <h3>Bank transfer</h3>
    <p>
      You can transfer directly to our account at Unity Trust Bank.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Account name: <strong>Mountain Heritage Trust</strong></li>
      <li>Sort code: <strong>60-83-01</strong></li>
      <li>Account number: <strong>20495831</strong></li>
      <li>Reference: please use your surname followed by <code>MHT</code> — e.g. <code>Smith MHT</code>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Cheque</h3>
    <p>
      Make cheques payable to <strong>Mountain Heritage Trust</strong> and post to:
    </p>
    <address class="contact-details">
      Mountain Heritage Trust<br />
      Blencathra Field Centre<br />
      Threlkeld<br />
      Keswick<br />
      Cumbria CA12 4SG
    </address>

    <h2>Gift Aid</h2>
    <p>
      If you are a UK taxpayer, Gift Aid increases the value of your donation by 25% at
      no cost to you. Donations made through JustGiving have Gift Aid handled
      automatically. For bank transfers and cheques, please email
      <a href="mailto:enquiries@mountain-heritage.org">enquiries@mountain-heritage.org</a>
      and we will send you a Gift Aid declaration form.
    </p>

    <h2>Donate objects and archives</h2>
    <p>
      Our collections grow through the generosity of climbers, families and clubs who
      entrust us with the objects and records of Britain's mountaineering past. If you
      have something that helps tell that story, we would love to hear from you.
    </p>
    <p>We are particularly interested in material such as:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Climbing and mountaineering equipment — ice axes, ropes, boots, crampons and early protection.</li>
      <li>Clothing and personal kit, especially items used on notable climbs or expeditions.</li>
      <li>Photographs, films, slides and albums.</li>
      <li>Diaries, logbooks, letters, and expedition or club records.</li>
      <li>Books, guidebooks, journals and artwork.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Every item is different and we can't take everything, so please don't send
      anything before speaking to us. Tell us a little about what you have and we will
      talk you through the options. <a href="/contact">Get in touch</a> to start the
      conversation.
    </p>

    <h2>Other ways to help</h2>
    <p>
      We welcome volunteers — to work alongside the archivist at the office, or to help
      spread awareness of the Trust's work at events, climbing walls and clubs. If you
      would like to get involved, please <a href="/contact">get in touch</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
